item.title: A bit about me..
item.dc:creator: bekskinner95
item.content:encoded:
Hi I'm Bek, the face behind Bek Curated.

I first started 'Bek Curated' as a creative Instagram, where I posted curated photos of my life and the things I love and do. This was because I felt as though it was a curated version from that of my personal Instagram and a way to show how the curation of images can tell ones story. Im a freelance creative and stylist based in Sydney, Australia. I am also a Communications student at the University of Technology Sydney, where I major in Digital and Social Media. I have been working in fashion since the age of 16 and more recently have been interning in fashion marketing and pursuing freelance styling. With my interests, studies, internships and travels it would only make sense that I start this blog and share my experiences and opportunities with you in hope to be a starting point of inspiration for those who wish to pursue a career in the fashion industry. Not only that, I love to be able to showcase my work to potential future employers/clients and likeminded people that may wish to get in touch. I hope you enjoy what I provide you with on this blog and I hope you can follow me on my journey.

Bek xo

item.title: Living in New York City
item.dc:creator: bekskinner95
item.content:encoded:
How one of the biggest fashion hubs of the world changed my life..

'New York City is not just a city, it's a world'

Anyone thats been to New York City before, know that its not a city that can be easily described, explained and definitely one that can not be used in any comparison.

item.title: How I became fashion obsessed
item.dc:creator: bekskinner95
item.content:encoded:
I first began my fashion journey at the age of 16, where I got my first retail job. It was at a place called "Novo" shoes. Immediately I fell in love with the idea of having to dress myself presentably and purchase shoes from the brand to wear in which was for marketing purposes. I guess this was my first taste or what it means to market a brand.
To keep it short and simple, I stayed in shoes until I secured my next job, which actually happened quite funnily. I was shopping in Lovisa, where I used my own customer skills to create a relationship with the worker, who was actually, not to my knowledge at the time, a state manager. When I got to the counter to purchase my items she asked me if I would be interested working for the company. For me, I loved my job, but Lovisa was something I held in a high light, I loved the brand, I thought everyone that worked there was cool, I absolutely loved the stuff and I just couldn't not find out more.

Long story short again, I had a successful few years at Lovisa, until I was poached again by "Glassons".... an absolute DREAM. Every girl working at Glassons, at Erina Fair on the Central Coast was considered an IT girl. The style was amazing, the girls were amazing, and you could actually see people working there moving forward in their career into head office and other roles. It was honestly life changing. It sounds dramatic, but my life and who I am today would never be the same if this moment in my life didn't happen.

I began my Glassons journey, and here I am today, 7 years later still working for the brand while I finish my degree. I hope to one day, if not now, but down the track still be a part of the company, but within the creative and digital team.

My time at Glassons has taught me customer service, styling, marketing, social media and its been the time of my life. I've learnt content creation, in which I am obsessed with....

I've also learnt visual merchandising, management and business. All of this in which has been perfectly inline with my digital marketing degree and wanting to pursue a career in fashion marketing. Its honestly true that everything happens for a reason and its important to listen to the signs in your life and use them as the stepping stones to building your dream life. Most people look at casual work growing up as a way to make some money for the weekend, or something that their parents made them too. For me, mines all been beneficial towards my career today, from where it began to where it is now. There is not a single place, or thing I've learnt that won't help me with my future career and for that I am so incredibly thankful.

item.title: New York City MUSTS
item.dc:creator: bekskinner95
item.content:encoded:
How to become a New York City socialite.. One of my favourite things, and the first thing you should do when you land in New York City is visit the SoHo district. This by far is my favourite place in the whole of NYC. Shopping and walking around SoHo, you are almost for sure going to someone of celeb status and if you dont, I can assure you you are going to feel like a celeb yourself. The vibe, the shops, the cafes, pretty much to sum it up, its the part of NYC that you see all over Pinterest, Twitter and Instagram. Your going to want to be photo ready - every wall, every street, every cafe - Instaworthy

Visit DUMBO - Brooklyn.
You may be wondering "what is DUMBO?", if you haven't been to NYC. However, once you visit DUMBO, you'll wonder why this isn't a phrase thats thrown around more often.

Dumbo is essentially under the Brooklyn Bridge, on the Brooklyn side, and is home to some of the best pizza you'll ever eat!

Its an absolute NYC must to get a slice of take out pizza, take it to the grass over under the Brooklyn Bridge and sit and enjoy the views of Manhattan. This would have to be one of the most pictured picnic spots in the world.

Go to as many rooftop bars as possible! The atmosphere is insane and if you want to get that, OMG I'm in NYC and on top of the world feeling, then this is where you'll find it!

Some rooftop bars I can recommend are PHD Midtown, Refinery Rooftop Midtown, Moxy Times Square, Spyglass, 230 Fifth, The Standard, Azul, just to name a few....
